name: bulk-data-tools/.esdoc.js
bulk-data-tools/csv.js
isObject
description: Tests if the given argument is an object

name: getPath
description:
Walks thru an object (ar array) and returns the value found at the
provided path. This function is very simple so it intentionally does not
support any argument polymorphism, meaning that the path can only be a
dot-separated string. If the path is invalid returns undefined.

unknown.tagValue: {*} Whatever is found in the path or undefined

params.name: obj
params.description: The object (or Array) to walk through

return.description: Whatever is found in the path or undefined

name: escapeCsvValue
description:
Escapes a value as CSV value
- If it contains a double quote, new line or separator (typically a comma),
  the value is quoted
- any contained quotes are escaped with another quote
- undefined is converted to empty string
- everything else is converted to string (but is not quoted)

name: flatObjectKeys
description:
Returns a flattened array of the structure of an object or array.
For example:
```js
{a:1, b:{c:2,d:3}, e:4} -> ["a", "b.c", "b.d", "e"]
{a:1, b:[ 2, 3 ], e: 4} -> ["a", "b.0", "b.1", "e"]
[1, {a: 3, b: 4}, 2, 3] -> ["0", "1.a", "1.b", "2", "3"]
```

params.name: _prefix
params.description:
Path prefix that if provided, will be prepended to
each key. Please do not use this argument. The function will pass it to
itself on recursive calls.

name: mergeStrict
description:
Merges the second argument into the first one but also throws if an object
property is about to be overridden with scalar (or the opposite).

throws.description:
If a path in one object points to scalar value and the same
path in the other object points to an object (or the opposite).

name: csvHeaderFromArray
description:
Loops over an array of objects or arrays (rows) and builds a header that
matches the structure of the rows.

unknown.tagValue: {String[]} The header as an array of strings

params.name: array
params.description: The array of row objects or arrays

params.name: options.fast
params.description:
If true, assumes that all rows have the same
structure and only use the first one to build the header.

return.description: The header as an array of strings

description:
Returns the int representation of the first argument or the
"defaultValue" if the int conversion is not possible.

params.name: defaultValue
params.description:

converted to integer too.

description:

"defaultValue" if the int conversion is not possible.

params.name: defaultValue
params.description:
The fall-back return value. This is going to be
converted to float too.
